FT  16 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Beauford back in black
An improving order intake helped Beauford return to profit in the six months
to June 30.
On sales of Pounds 15.7m (Pounds 13.4m) from continuing operations, the
engineering and ceramics group achieved pre-tax profits of Pounds 851,000
(Pounds 3.06m loss) including an exceptional credit from the sale of the
Clayton stake of Pounds 362,000. But interest took Pounds 313,000 (Pounds
503,000).
Earnings per share came through at 3.9p (38.27p loss).
